    <div class="govuk-grid-row">
        <div class="govuk-grid-column-two-thirds">

            <h1 class="govuk-heading-xl">Privacy notice for Confirm my apprenticeship details</h1>
            <p class="govuk-body">
                This privacy notice explains how we collect and use your personal information for the My apprenticeship service.
                This service is run by the Education and Skills Funding Agency (ESFA), an executive agency of the Department for
                Education (DfE).
            </p>
            <p class="govuk-body">
                For the purposes of the relevant data protection legislation, DfE is the data controller for any personal information
                processed on this service.
            </p>

            <h2 class="govuk-heading-m">How we use your personal information</h2>
            <p class="govuk-body">
                DfE collects your personal information when you use the My apprenticeship service.
            </p>
            <p class="govuk-body">
                We use your personal information so the DfE can carry out its functions.
            </p>
            <p class="govuk-body">
                When you register on the service, the personal information you give us will be used:
            </p>

            <ul class="govuk-list govuk-list--bullet">
                <li>to match you to the details of your apprenticeship as provided by your employer and training provider</li>
                <li>to provide help and support during the use of the service</li>
                <li>to notify you of specific in-service updates and actions with regard to your apprenticeship</li>
                <li>to contact you for feedback on services we provide to you</li>
                <li>for administration and research purposes</li>
                <li>to ensure the protection of public funds</li>
                <li>to prevent and detect fraud</li>
            </ul>

            <p class="govuk-body">We collect and use the following personal information only where we need to, and law permits:</p>

            <ul class="govuk-list govuk-list--bullet">
                <li>first name</li>
                <li>last name</li>
                <li>date of birth</li>
                <li>unique learner number</li>
                <li>email address</li>
            </ul>

            <h2 class="govuk-heading-m">How long we hold personal information</h2>
            <p class="govuk-body">
                We will only keep your personal data for as long as we need it.
                ESFA has a disposal schedule for personal data based on the needs of the agency and the law.
                We may need to keep some of your personal data for 66 years for research and producing statistics.
            </p>
            <p class="govuk-body">
                We will take necessary steps to keep your information safe.
                It will then be securely destroyed when it is no longer needed.
            </p>
            <p class="govuk-body">
                If you need further information about how long the ESFA holds personal information for, read the
                <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/esfa-privacy-notice/esfa-privacy-notice">ESFA privacy notice</a>.
            </p>

            <h2 class="govuk-heading-m">Who we share your personal information with</h2>
            <p class="govuk-body">
                We may share your information where the law allows it to enable the running of the
                Confirm my apprenticeship details service, or where we have a legal obligation to do so.
            </p>
            <p class="govuk-body">
                If you need further information about who the ESFA shares your personal data with, read the
                <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/esfa-privacy-notice/esfa-privacy-notice">ESFA privacy notice</a>.
            </p>

            <h2 class="govuk-heading-m">Our legal basis for collecting and processing the data</h2>
            <p class="govuk-body">
                For the use of personal data to be lawful, we need to meet one (or more) conditions in the data protection legislation,
                as set out in Article 6(1) of the General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR). For the purpose of My apprenticeship service,
                the relevant condition that we are meeting is &lsquo;public task&lsquo; as specified under Article 6 (1)(e) of the GDPR.
            </p>

            <h2 class="govuk-heading-m">Your data protection rights</h2>
            <p class="govuk-body">
                Under data protection law, you have certain rights depending on our reason for processing your personal information.
                You have the right to:
            </p>

            <ul class="govuk-list govuk-list--bullet">
                <li>
                    access - you have the right to ask us for copies of your personal information -
                    <a href="https://ico.org.uk/for-organisations/guide-to-data-protection/guide-to-the-general-data-protection-regulation-gdpr/individual-rights/right-of-access/">more about right of access</a>
                </li>
                <li>have your personal data rectified, if it is inaccurate or incomplete</li>
                <li>request the deletion or removal of personal data where there is no compelling reason for its continued processing</li>
                <li>restrict our processing of your personal data (that is permitting its storage but no further processing)</li>
                <li>object to processing - you have the right to object to the processing of your personal information in certain circumstances</li>
                <li>data portability - you have the right to ask that we transfer the personal information you gave us to another organisation, or to you, in certain circumstances</li>
            </ul>

            <p class="govuk-body">
                If you have any of these requests, you can <a href="https://www.gov.uk/contact-dfe">contact us at the DfE</a>.
            </p>

            <p class="govuk-body">
                You can read more information about
                <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/organisations/department-for-education/about/personal-information-charter">how the DfE handles personal information</a>.
            </p>

            <p class="govuk-body">
                You can also read further information about your data protection rights on the
                <a href="https://ico.org.uk/for-organisations/guide-to-data-protection/guide-to-the-general-data-protection-regulation-gdpr/principles/#the_principles">Information Commissioner’s website</a>.
            </p>

            <h2 class="govuk-heading-m">How to complain</h2>

            <p class="govuk-body">
                Contact us using our <a href="https://www.education.gov.uk/contactus/efa">secure online contact form</a>
                or by writing to the DfE’s Data Protection Officer (DPO) at:
            </p>

            <p class="govuk-body">
                Ministerial and Public Communications Division<br />
                Department for Education<br />
                Piccadilly Gate<br />
                Store Street<br />
                Manchester<br />
                M1 2WD
            </p>

            <p class="govuk-body">
                You also have the right to <a href="https://ico.org.uk/make-a-complaint/">make a complaint</a> to the Information Commissioner's Office.
            </p>

            <p class="govuk-body">This privacy notice was prepared on 15/07/2020.</p>
